{
  "texts": [
    "For concreteness, we orient this line (we will also refer to this as a DW) along the a 2 direction, and let the sublattice potential vary along the a 1 direction such that sgn(∆(r)) = -sgn(x 1), where x 1 is the spatial coordinate along a 1.",
    "We label the region x 1 < 0 to the left of the DW as L, and label the region on the other side as R. The sublattice potential is taken to be +∆ max deep inside region L, and -∆ max deep inside region R. An example choice of sublattice potential profile consists of linearly interpolating between these values over a length scale 2w.",
    "This leads to ∆(x 1) = -∆ max x 1 /w for small x 1.Within the 'bulk' of each region |x 1 | ≫ w, we anticipate that the system will locally form a spin-valley polarized QAH state.",
    "We assume that the spin is polarized along ↑ everywhere due to spin exchange physics.",
    "Hence, it remains to determine the spontaneous valley polarization within each domain."
  ]
}